node.text:
A tutorial for my 5 minute face using the @ecotools BioBlender makeup sponge! If I only have 5 minutes (which is more often than not) I like to focus on my skin! The BioBlender is super soft and bouncy and creates a gorgeous, seamless look! The 4 edge design is so versatile, it’s eco-friendly, and affordable!! Link below to shop at @Walmart! #ad

Shop BioBlender here! https://bit.ly/3k3KOjY

node.text:
Here are a few healthy suhoor ideas that will hopefully get you through the end of Ramadan! •

Mini Omelet Bites: 
modified from this recipe: https://www.wellplated.com/healthy-br...
(I used a mini muffin tin rather than the larger 12 cup , so took only 15 minutes to bake) •

Chocolate Chia Seed Pudding: 
2 tbsp cacao powder , or cocoa powder
3 tbsp maple syrup
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 cup dairy-free milk
1/4 cup chia seeds 
garnish with berries or nuts!

No Bake Energy Bars:
13-14 medium medjool pitted dates (about 1 1/2 cups)
1 cup raw walnuts
1 cup old fashioned rolled oats 
1/4 cup peanut butter 
1/4 cup flax seed powder (optional to add fiber)
1/4 cup unsweetened coconut flakes 
3 tbsp cacao or cocoa powder
1/4 tsp salt

Green Smoothie:
1 frozen banana
1/2 cup frozen mango
1 cup fresh spinach
fresh ginger (size of end of finger)
squeeze of half a lime 
coconut water (or just plain water!) to desired consistency

1 bunch asparagus 
Season with: 
garlic salt
black pepper
rosemary 
olive oil

node.text: Alaina’s birthday party was a success 🥰 not only did we celebrate our princess but we also celebrated making it through one year of parenthood for Omar and I because this stuff is HARD! We made it through the sleepless nights, adjusted to our new roles, supported each other when we felt like we were at our breaking point. Our lives changed (for the better) forever last August and thank God we made it! May God protect all of our children make them healthy and happy always!!! Ameen! That’s truly all that matters 💗💗💗
